            '[19:13] Leviathan - Thomas Hobbes.epub (Leviathan_split_049.html) - 19.13',
            'This ceremony was not therefore new in our Saviours time. For Jairus (Mark 5.23.) whose daughter was sick, besought our Saviour (not to heal her, but) "to Lay his Hands upon her, that shee might bee healed." And (Matth. <<19.13|5a:0>>.) "they brought unto him little children, that hee should Put his Hands on them, and Pray."',
